This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Jimmy Morales of Guatemala, President Salvador Sánchez Cerén of El Salvador, President Juan Orlando Hernández of Honduras, and Vice President Mike Pence of the United States. They discuss various topics including the eruption of the Fuego Volcano in Guatemala, migration, border strengthening, and the fight against drug trafficking. They express gratitude for the support and aid provided by the United States and other countries in response to the volcano eruption. They also discuss the need to address the root causes of migration, strengthen borders, and combat criminal organizations. Vice President Pence emphasizes the importance of following immigration laws and the need for cooperation between the United States and Central American countries to end the migration crisis. The leaders also discuss the importance of economic development and job creation in the region.